What does it mean for two vectors to be orthogonal? Is there more than one direction that is orthogonal to a given vector?
Two orthogonal vectors can each be orthogonal to a third vector. Construct a model of this situation using three pencils. Can you do this successfully while keeping all the vectors aligned along the surface of a table?

